callout.xt:author: Ian Findlay
callout.p: Duty point refers to the design flow and pressure in the system served by the fan.
Selection point refers to the point where the selected fan curve intersects the system curve.

Operating point refers to the duty flow and pressure if the fan is a variable speed fan, or to the point on the applicable fan curve where the fan flow equals the duty flow, if the fan is a fixed speed fan.
